ANDY: <i>Freel was like</i> a <i>leper
crashing</i> a <i>hot tub party.</i>

16:26.486 --> 16:29.113
<i>The only one who stood his ground
was The Stort,</i>

16:29.238 --> 16:32.200
<i>knowing full well he was the only one
that could save Free! now.</i>

16:32.283 --> 16:33.493
I need you, man! You gotta help me!

16:33.576 --> 16:35.077
Shut up, man! Shut up!

16:35.203 --> 16:37.497
This isn't going to be easy, man.
Here's what you've got to do.

16:39.707 --> 16:40.875
You gotta touch her again...

16:41.000 --> 16:42.668
No, man. No way!

16:42.793 --> 16:43.836
I won't! I can't!

16:43.920 --> 16:45.213
There's gotta be another way!

16:45.296 --> 16:48.299
Shut up, Freel! Shut up, you loser!
There's only one way!

16:49.091 --> 16:50.885
You gotta touch her again
and say the words,

16:51.010 --> 16:53.513
"From this the cooties came,
with this the cooties shall remain."

16:54.931 --> 16:57.350
Freel! I'm losing you, man!
Stay focused!

16:57.475 --> 16:59.519
Okay, Okay---

17:00.478 --> 17:02.897
-"With this the cooties came..."
-"From this," you idiot.

17:03.022 --> 17:05.691
"From this the cooties came,
with this the cooties shall remain."

17:05.816 --> 17:07.151
Okay, Okay---

17:08.319 --> 17:09.529
From this. From this...

17:10.488 --> 17:12.073
All right, I got it! Thanks, man!
I owe you one!

17:12.156 --> 17:13.657
Hey, Freel, one last thing.

17:15.242 --> 17:16.911
You've got to do it on her territory.

17:18.454 --> 17:19.497
Geek Corner?

17:19.872 --> 17:21.082
Yeah. Geek Corner.

17:22.708 --> 17:24.126
Why don't you just give Ricky Brown
your lunch?

17:24.252 --> 17:25.544
Or do his homework?

17:25.545 --> 17:26.546
Cut some kind of deal with him.

17:26.628 --> 17:27.672
Because it's not right.

17:28.548 --> 17:31.551
Right? What does that have to do
with getting our asses kicked?

17:31.759 --> 17:34.345
Damn it, Stanley! Why do you have
to make things so tough on yourself?

17:35.054 --> 17:36.264
You shouldn't swear, Norman.

17:36.347 --> 17:38.474
Do you mind? I'd like to get going.

17:38.558 --> 17:39.559
Oh, right. Sorry.

17:39.684 --> 17:42.061
Didn't want to keep you down here
any longer than you have to be.

17:42.144 --> 17:45.106
I mean, it's pretty courageous of you,
risking terminal cooties and all.

17:45.398 --> 17:46.565
What are your buddies gonna think?

17:46.566 --> 17:48.109
I got news for you, Normie.

17:48.568 --> 17:50.069
Even if you weren't a complete geek,

17:50.152 --> 17:52.488
people would still
beat the crap out of you!

17:52.572 --> 17:54.282
Stanley! Jason Freel's got Karen!

17:57.702 --> 17:58.744
(SHOUTING) From this
the cooties came...

17:58.869 --> 18:01.330
ANDY: <i>Freel recited
the absolving incantation</i>

18:01.414 --> 18:03.124
<i>as he whipped Karen with his jacket.</i>

18:03.583 --> 18:06.002
<i>He could not bring himself
to actually touch her, but then,</i>

18:06.502 --> 18:07.545
<i>who would know?</i>

18:07.670 --> 18:08.879
<i>He could always say he did.</i>

18:09.297 --> 18:10.590
...with this they shall remain!

18:12.800 --> 18:14.719
<i>With his feet dangling
a foot off the ground,</i>

18:14.802 --> 18:17.221
<i>Jason Freel found religion,</i>

18:17.346 --> 18:19.307
<i>and prayed to the Lord Big G.</i>

18:19.390 --> 18:21.017
Break his neck! No, no, wait!

18:21.142 --> 18:23.352
Let me get some of his friends to watch,
then break his neck!

18:26.022 --> 18:27.189
(PANTING)

18:29.442 --> 18:30.568
(SCREAMS) No!

18:37.366 --> 18:38.409
No.

18:44.540 --> 18:45.916
Are you completely insane?

18:46.626 --> 18:47.793
You had him!

18:47.918 --> 18:49.211
You could have broken him in two!

18:49.337 --> 18:52.548
I mean, you could have at least held him
and I hit him with a brick or something.

18:54.467 --> 18:55.635
Do you want to work
some more on the project?

18:56.427 --> 18:58.137
Norman's right. I don't get it.

18:58.220 --> 19:01.641
Why do you let guys like Freel and Ricky
always make fun of you all the time?

19:02.642 --> 19:04.852
I can't make them be nice people.

19:04.977 --> 19:07.563
And even if I did,
there'd be others to take their place.

19:13.653 --> 19:16.280
If I had Big G's body,
I'd have kicked Freel's ass!

19:16.739 --> 19:19.075
Then, I'd have kicked Ricky Brown's ass
just to cool down.

19:22.161 --> 19:23.204
You probably thought it was funny.

19:26.499 --> 19:28.793
No. I didn't.

19:30.252 --> 19:32.630
Screw it. So Freel beats me up?

19:33.172 --> 19:35.007
He was probably
going to do that anyway.

19:35.841 --> 19:37.093
I'm telling Mr Simon.

19:41.305 --> 19:42.640
(SNIFFS)

19:43.224 --> 19:44.684
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

19:45.685 --> 19:46.686
Karen?

19:47.687 --> 19:48.813
Karen, it's Mr Simon.

20:00.866 --> 20:02.076
Karen, I'm coming in, honey.

20:03.077 --> 20:04.995
Please go away, Mr Simon.

20:06.038 --> 20:07.081
I'll be okay.

20:23.723 --> 20:25.724
I'm going to open the door, sweetheart.

20:25.725 --> 20:26.725
Please go away.

20:26.726 --> 20:29.270
No, I'm going to open the door. It's okay.

20:36.736 --> 20:38.738
Here. Give me your hand, sweetheart.

20:39.530 --> 20:40.573
Come on.

20:42.116 --> 20:44.076
Don't let them see you like this.

20:52.752 --> 20:54.128
It's okay.

20:57.465 --> 20:58.924
What happened to you?

21:01.719 --> 21:02.928
Who did this to you?

21:06.766 --> 21:10.561
ANDY: <i>The word had spread quickly
that Mr Simon was extremely upset,</i>

21:10.686 --> 21:11.896
<i>and that it was quite possible</i>

21:11.979 --> 21:15.107
<i>Jason Freel would receive
his final report card</i>

21:15.191 --> 21:16.567
<i>in federal prison.</i>

21:24.784 --> 21:28.287
Some of the cuts
on Karen's arms and neck

21:28.370 --> 21:31.373
made by the zipper
from Mr Freel's jacket

21:31.499 --> 21:34.168
are deeper than first thought,

21:34.293 --> 21:38.297
and she has been sent to the doctor's.

21:48.808 --> 21:50.810
For anyone interested,

21:51.811 --> 21:53.813
this is how I won the car.

22:01.987 --> 22:04.657
ANDY: <i>The newspaper contest
to win the new car</i>

22:04.782 --> 22:09.537
<i>asked contestants to find a solution
to world peace using 25 words or less.</i>

22:11.330 --> 22:14.041
<i>Mr Simon won it with just four.</i>

22:35.855 --> 22:38.691
I really don't feel
much like teaching today.

22:40.401 --> 22:42.361
It's a rather strange feeling.

22:43.612 --> 22:49.410
I suggest if you have a book,
now would be a good time to read.

22:51.829 --> 22:54.248
And if you don't, well...

22:57.418 --> 22:59.879
Well, you should always
have a book with you.

23:14.894 --> 23:16.896
<i>(DREAMING OF YOU PLPOHNG)</i>

24:04.276 --> 24:05.861
Can I help you with something, bud?

24:06.737 --> 24:08.781
Sir, sorry.

24:08.906 --> 24:12.159
I kind of missed your porch,
and I was just gonna put it on...

24:12.284 --> 24:15.871
You know, it's funny, I've been
watching you deliver your papers there,

24:16.121 --> 24:17.956
and you've got a hell of an arm,
by the way, kid.

24:17.957 --> 24:19.083
- Thank you.
-But somehow,

24:19.166 --> 24:21.585
you just seem to hit
everybody's porch but mine.

24:23.087 --> 24:24.713
You got any theories on that?

24:27.466 --> 24:28.968
I don't know.

24:29.259 --> 24:31.887
Maybe I'm just a little tired
by the time I get here, or...

24:31.971 --> 24:32.972
Daddy, dinner's ready.

24:34.390 --> 24:35.474
<i>ANDY". Even in eighth grade,</i>

24:35.557 --> 24:37.559
<i>there was a lot more woman
in Mary Clear</i>

24:37.685 --> 24:40.938
<i>than any eighth-grade boy
could possibly know what to do with.</i>

24:41.981 --> 24:43.315
<i>And I'm convinced she knew it.</i>

24:44.733 --> 24:46.068
<i>Maybe that was part of the fun.</i>

24:48.112 --> 24:49.405
Hi, Mary.

24:49.738 --> 24:52.992
I just... I threw the paper,
and your dad was just...

24:54.076 --> 24:55.911
Well, I'll just give it...

24:57.371 --> 24:58.789
Here. You know...

24:58.914 --> 24:59.957
There you go.

25:01.000 --> 25:04.503
I promise I won't miss next time,
Mr Clear.

25:05.004 --> 25:07.006
- You got to pace yourself, bud.
-Yeah.

25:15.556 --> 25:18.142
ANDY: <i>Every Friday,
I worked in the office during Study Hall.</i>

25:18.517 --> 25:22.312
<i>I'd run off copies of flyers to parents
announcing an open house,</i>

25:22.730 --> 25:26.358
<i>or reminders about the upcoming
car wash to raise money for the library.</i>

25:27.026 --> 25:29.987
<i>Generally, whatever annoying
little job Mrs Cranby,</i>

25:30.029 --> 25:33.866
<i>the assistant principal, affectionately
known as Old Tuna Breath,</i>

25:33.991 --> 25:35.200
<i>didn't feel like doing herself.</i>

25:35.325 --> 25:36.410
Andrew!

25:38.537 --> 25:41.039
Wait till you see the talent show
programme I've designed.

25:41.040 --> 25:43.542
I've never had so much fun in my life.

25:43.625 --> 25:47.171
If you could just run off 600 copies,
we'll be all set.

25:48.172 --> 25:51.049
We certainly have
an interesting turnout this year.

25:51.050 --> 25:52.593
It looks really nice, Mrs Cranby.

25:53.260 --> 25:55.804
Oh, Doris Gebben
plays the upright bass?

25:56.388 --> 25:58.766
Isn't that the really huge one?
She's, like, three feet tall.

25:58.849 --> 26:02.603
Yes, indeed. Tiny, but top notch.
I understand she's very good.

26:03.020 --> 26:05.064
Wait. Mrs Cranby, this can't be right.

26:05.397 --> 26:06.607
What? ls something misspelled?

26:07.691 --> 26:09.359
Big G's gonna...

26:11.070 --> 26:12.071
Gonna sing?

26:12.905 --> 26:13.989
Yes!

26:15.824 --> 26:18.869
I don't get it!
Your life isn't miserable enough as it is?

26:19.078 --> 26:22.081
So now you're going to get up in front
of the whole student body and sing?

26:22.372 --> 26:23.582
I love to sing.

26:23.665 --> 26:27.461
I've known you my whole life.
Never heard you sing. Not once.

26:27.586 --> 26:29.463
Since when do you love to sing?

26:29.588 --> 26:31.298
Ever since I can remember.

26:31.423 --> 26:32.800
Look, maybe...

26:33.425 --> 26:35.094
I don't know. Maybe Norman's right.

26:35.427 --> 26:37.888
I have a right to sing in the talent show,
just like anybody else.

26:38.013 --> 26:39.681
Don't you ever watch cop shows?

26:40.057 --> 26:41.475
You have the right to remain silent?

26:41.934 --> 26:43.811
You want to sing? Do it in the shower!

26:44.103 --> 26:46.730
Why don't you sing with a band?
Why do you have to sing all by yourself?

26:46.855 --> 26:49.107
I sing a cappella.
My voice is my instrument.

26:49.108 --> 26:50.859
Oh, my God!

26:51.110 --> 26:54.321
Why not just buy a gun and
let Ricky Brown shoot you in the eye?

26:54.446 --> 26:55.656
I knew
you wouldn't understand, Norman.

26:55.739 --> 26:57.032
That's why I didn't tell you about it.

26:57.116 --> 26:58.117
What about us?

26:58.617 --> 26:59.952
You sing in that stupid show,

27:00.077 --> 27:01.745
and it's just gonna make it worse
for the rest of us!

27:02.287 --> 27:05.916
It doesn't matter what they do to us.
You said it yourself, Norman.

27:05.999 --> 27:07.876
They'll probably just do it anyway.

27:09.753 --> 27:11.713
I think you should sing if you want to.

27:18.137 --> 27:19.805
I'm sorry, Norman, but I'm going to sing.

27:19.972 --> 27:21.139
Damn it, Stanley!

27:21.140 --> 27:23.142
Why do you have to make
everything harder than it is?

27:23.183 --> 27:24.935
- You shouldn't swear, Norman.
-Go to hell!

27:25.561 --> 27:26.812
You deserve whatever you get!

27:33.026 --> 27:34.903
I think he's just worried about you.

27:36.155 --> 27:39.158
Come on, there's a few more minutes
before the bell rings.

27:45.789 --> 27:48.333
Hey, Andy. Mary Clear likes you.

27:51.920 --> 27:53.338
Mary Clear likes me?

27:53.797 --> 27:54.965
That's what I said.

27:55.174 --> 27:57.176
- Why?
-"Why"?

27:58.177 --> 28:01.805
I don't know. She's pretty much
gone steady with everybody else, so...

28:02.181 --> 28:05.851
She told you that she wanted
to go steady with me?

28:05.976 --> 28:07.436
Of course! She's my best friend.

28:08.187 --> 28:11.064
She said she thinks you're cute.
And don't ask me why.

28:13.150 --> 28:14.193
Wow.

28:17.571 --> 28:21.950
ANDY: <i>Let's just say that
selection by process of elimination</i>

28:22.034 --> 28:25.537
<i>lacked a certain romance one might
otherwise have found exciting.</i>

28:26.371 --> 28:28.207
<i>Even at the age of 13.</i>

28:31.084 --> 28:33.211
<i>At the end of every month,
I had to collect money</i>

28:33.212 --> 28:35.339
<i>from all the customers on my route.</i>

28:35.839 --> 28:38.091
<i>It was a task I relished for its simplicity</i>

28:38.217 --> 28:41.094
<i>in what was becoming
an increasingly complicated world.</i>

28:41.595 --> 28:44.348
<i>Hit the porch
and the customer was satisfied.</i>

28:45.098 --> 28:47.225
<i>And a satisfied customer meant payoffs,</i>

28:47.226 --> 28:50.979
<i>ranging anywhere from cash tips
to assorted snack foods.</i>

28:55.400 --> 28:57.819
<i>Next stop, Mary Clear's house.</i>

28:58.237 --> 29:00.822
<i>Regardless of her sudden
and mysterious interest in me,</i>

29:01.240 --> 29:04.034
<i>coupled by the fact
that I had yet to hit her porch,</i>

29:04.868 --> 29:06.828
<i>I wasn't expecting much.</i>

29:11.250 --> 29:13.043
Hi, Andy. How's it going?

29:13.877 --> 29:15.671
Good. How's it going with you?

29:15.796 --> 29:16.838
Great.

29:17.422 --> 29:18.465
Good.

29:20.425 --> 29:22.636
So, uh, how's it going?

29:24.221 --> 29:25.681
You asked me that already.

29:26.598 --> 29:27.641
Oh, uh... Yeah.

29:29.017 --> 29:30.435
You said "great", right?

29:30.519 --> 29:31.687
Yeah.

29:31.812 --> 29:36.274
Okay. So, is your mom or dad home?
I'm collecting for the paper.

29:36.275 --> 29:37.276
Oh, yeah. Here you go.

29:39.403 --> 29:42.906
Oh, okay, thanks.

29:46.535 --> 29:48.245
- There you go.
-Thanks.

29:49.246 --> 29:52.249
All right, well, I gotta get going.

29:52.291 --> 29:53.333
Yeah, I'll see you at school.

29:54.668 --> 29:56.712
Yeah. Yeah, okay.

29:57.421 --> 29:59.131
I'll... I'll see you.

30:56.897 --> 30:58.565
Hey, Nichol.
I see you're collecting for the paper.

30:59.358 --> 31:00.567
Why'd you have to do that, Ricky?

31:01.360 --> 31:02.778
I didn't have to.

31:02.903 --> 31:04.363
It was my treat. What's in the bag?

31:06.365 --> 31:09.326
Don't get up. I'll just have to
knock you back down again.

31:13.955 --> 31:14.998
Chocolate chip.

31:15.707 --> 31:17.918
My favourite. See you in school, Nichol.

31:22.214 --> 31:24.007
DAN: So, she paid you the money?

31:25.384 --> 31:29.387
Yeah. Which means Mary had to ask
her parents for the money in advance.

31:29.388 --> 31:30.389
It was a set-up.

31:31.139 --> 31:32.432
Barbara Foss wasn't blowing smoke.

31:33.809 --> 31:34.851
Mary likes me.

31:35.352 --> 31:36.395
And this is a bad thing?

31:37.145 --> 31:39.356
I don't know. It's weird.

31:39.398 --> 31:41.650
I'm no different than I was
at the beginning of the year.

31:41.858 --> 31:44.611
And I just...
I mean, I've never even talked to her.

31:46.238 --> 31:48.240
What does that have to do
with anything?

31:48.365 --> 31:50.617
I don't know. ltjust seems like it should.

31:53.578 --> 31:55.414
You gonna kiss her?

31:57.416 --> 31:59.251
Yeah. Of course I'm gonna kiss her.

31:59.376 --> 32:02.212
- Idiot.
-You know, she's a real good kisser.

32:02.838 --> 32:03.880
How would you know?

32:04.005 --> 32:06.675
You're probably the only other guy
in the school that hasn't kissed her yet.

32:06.800 --> 32:08.802
Yeah, right,
like she made out with Big G.

32:08.885 --> 32:09.970
I doubt it.

32:10.554 --> 32:11.805
He's probably up before you are.

32:12.556 --> 32:13.974
Shut up, Andy.

32:14.057 --> 32:16.393
You and Big G
are real bosom buddies now, huh?

32:16.601 --> 32:17.644
You shut up.

32:17.769 --> 32:20.105
I bet you never kissed a girl
in your life, have you, Nichol?

32:21.189 --> 32:23.442
Hey, Freel's back from suspension.

32:24.025 --> 32:25.444
(ALL CHATTERING)

32:32.492 --> 32:33.577
Hey, Nichol.

32:34.870 --> 32:36.621
How's that paper coming
in Simon's class?

32:37.914 --> 32:38.999
Okay.

32:40.041 --> 32:42.085
Remember you told me
Mr Simon was your favourite teacher?

32:42.586 --> 32:44.337
- Yeah.
-Still think so?

32:44.463 --> 32:45.672
After he stuck you with Big G?

32:46.465 --> 32:48.508
I don't know. I guess so.

32:48.884 --> 32:50.051
I don't get you, Andy.

32:50.135 --> 32:51.720
You know,
my dad says Simon's a homo.

32:52.471 --> 32:54.472
<i>ANDY". I had no idea what Modak meant,</i>

32:54.473 --> 32:56.850
<i>but I sensed from his tone
