I know. But I can't stop myself.

01:08:29.104 --> 01:08:32.108
ANDY: <i>Finally, up ahead,
I approached the tunnel.</i>

01:08:32.274 --> 01:08:35.028
<i>Mary would be waiting
on the other side.</i>

01:08:35.278 --> 01:08:36.529
You lost, Nichol?

01:08:36.613 --> 01:08:39.240
<i>They say your life flashes
before your eyes just prior to death,</i>

01:08:39.323 --> 01:08:41.242
<i>but that didn't happen to me.</i>

01:08:41.326 --> 01:08:42.618
<i>I took it as a good sign.</i>

01:08:42.660 --> 01:08:44.828
<i>All I could think about
was how painful it felt</i>

01:08:44.912 --> 01:08:47.372
<i>when Ricky had punched me
in the stomach.</i>

01:08:47.497 --> 01:08:48.624
<i>And that was just a warning.</i>

01:08:48.625 --> 01:08:50.042
Let him go, Ricky!

01:08:50.335 --> 01:08:52.127
Shut up, Mary! This ain't your business!

01:08:52.252 --> 01:08:54.171
You let him go,
or I'll tell Principal Kelner

01:08:54.296 --> 01:08:57.634
who stole $32 in quarters
out of the Pepsi machine.

01:08:59.761 --> 01:09:02.095
You're the luckiest butt wipe
I've ever known, Nichol.

01:09:02.180 --> 01:09:03.680
First a freak bails you out, now a girl?

01:09:03.765 --> 01:09:05.850
Am I gonna have to
fight your mother next?

01:09:06.643 --> 01:09:08.685
I bet the house on my mother, Ricky.

01:09:09.770 --> 01:09:12.939
You'll be alone next time, Nichol.
I promise.

01:09:16.653 --> 01:09:19.322
ANDY: <i>Having cheated death
once more, I marched on.</i>

01:09:19.404 --> 01:09:21.741
<i>At this point,
I wasn't sure who I feared most,</i>

01:09:21.866 --> 01:09:23.993
<i>Ricky Brown or Mary Clear.</i>

01:09:24.661 --> 01:09:26.953
<i>Whoever chose this particular spot
to make out</i>

01:09:27.080 --> 01:09:30.666
<i>knew a heck of a lot more about
symbolism than most eighth graders.</i>

01:09:30.667 --> 01:09:33.211
<i>Although no one knew
the origin of said tradition,</i>

01:09:33.336 --> 01:09:36.089
<i>my guess is that
it was Mary Clear herself.</i>

01:09:38.508 --> 01:09:40.926
<i>She alone would understand
its meaning.</i>

01:09:42.095 --> 01:09:43.179
Hi.

01:09:44.346 --> 01:09:45.890
We're gonna have to do this
after the talent show.

01:09:45.973 --> 01:09:47.809
My bus is leaving in one minute.

01:09:47.934 --> 01:09:49.685
Meet me back here.

01:10:07.954 --> 01:10:10.707
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

01:10:14.711 --> 01:10:17.171
Doris? Have you seen Big G?

01:10:17.588 --> 01:10:19.632
Yeah, I passed him
sitting out in the parking lot.

01:10:19.716 --> 01:10:20.967
Thank you.

01:10:43.614 --> 01:10:44.741
Stanley?

01:10:46.951 --> 01:10:48.202
Hello.

01:10:51.664 --> 01:10:52.749
You know that time Ricky Brown

01:10:52.832 --> 01:10:54.751
was squirting you in the crotch
with a water pistol?

01:10:56.461 --> 01:10:57.670
Yeah.

01:10:59.005 --> 01:11:01.758
I should have done something.
I should have tried to help you and...

01:11:03.050 --> 01:11:04.218
I'm sorry.

01:11:08.097 --> 01:11:09.265
That's okay.

01:11:13.853 --> 01:11:15.396
You scared?

01:11:16.272 --> 01:11:17.482
Yes.

01:11:19.400 --> 01:11:22.779
I think you may be
the bravest guy I know.

01:11:24.781 --> 01:11:26.532
Or the craziest.

01:11:26.824 --> 01:11:27.992
Yeah.

01:11:28.618 --> 01:11:30.244
Did Norman come?

01:11:32.288 --> 01:11:34.832
I don't know, but I'm sure he will.

01:11:35.291 --> 01:11:37.001
Yeah. It's funny.

01:11:37.835 --> 01:11:40.046
The smallest kid in school
protecting the biggest.

01:11:42.757 --> 01:11:43.800
Yeah.

01:11:45.718 --> 01:11:46.803
I'll see you after the show.

01:11:46.886 --> 01:11:49.764
Yeah. See you after the show.

01:12:04.821 --> 01:12:06.113
(CLEARS THROAT)

01:12:07.865 --> 01:12:12.370
<i>I want to thank everyone
for this marvellous turnout.</i>

01:12:12.495 --> 01:12:14.830
<i>The children have worked very hard,</i>

01:12:14.831 --> 01:12:18.584
<i>and I think you'll be surprised
at the wonderful variety</i>

01:12:18.709 --> 01:12:21.837
<i>of different acts
that we have for you tonight.</i>

01:12:21.838 --> 01:12:24.841
<i>Our first act is Doris Gebben,</i>

01:12:25.466 --> 01:12:29.929
<i>who will play a lovely Beethoven piece
on the stand-up bass.</i>

01:12:30.763 --> 01:12:31.848
<i>Doris.</i>

01:12:54.287 --> 01:12:56.080
(PLAYS OFF TUNE)

01:12:57.373 --> 01:12:59.083
Wait, wait. Sorry.

01:13:08.342 --> 01:13:10.928
ANDY: <i>As Doris droned on,
I searched the crowd for Norman,</i>

01:13:11.012 --> 01:13:12.889
<i>but he was nowhere to be found.</i>

01:13:15.558 --> 01:13:19.562
<i>I knew how much it meant to Stanley
for him to be there, so...</i>

01:13:46.255 --> 01:13:47.840
Collecting for the paper again?

01:13:47.924 --> 01:13:48.925
How come you're not
at the talent show?

01:13:48.966 --> 01:13:50.343
Why aren't you?

01:13:50.426 --> 01:13:51.927
He wanted to know if you were there,

01:13:51.928 --> 01:13:53.554
and when I didn't see you,
I just came here.

01:13:55.348 --> 01:13:57.266
You know those western movies
where the bad guys

01:13:57.391 --> 01:13:59.393
are gonna hang the good guy?

01:13:59.477 --> 01:14:01.395
But the posse shows up
to save the good guy just in time?

01:14:01.687 --> 01:14:02.897
Yeah.

01:14:02.939 --> 01:14:05.942
I guarantee you there's no posse
out looking to save Stanley.

01:14:06.943 --> 01:14:09.028
Look, I think he'll feel bad
if you're not there.

01:14:09.153 --> 01:14:11.364
I don't know why he does it.

01:14:11.447 --> 01:14:13.908
He just won't give in,
no matter what they do to him.

01:14:16.285 --> 01:14:17.620
He'll be on soon.

01:14:21.248 --> 01:14:24.627
I just don't want to see their faces.
I don't want to hear them laugh.

01:14:27.004 --> 01:14:29.965
Look, if he's brave enough to do it,

01:14:29.966 --> 01:14:32.009
I think you should be brave enough
to be there for him.

01:14:33.260 --> 01:14:34.845
And maybe...

01:14:36.305 --> 01:14:37.848
Maybe we're the posse.

01:14:38.975 --> 01:14:39.976
You don't know what it's like.

01:14:40.059 --> 01:14:43.521
No. But I do know
you and Stanley are best friends.

01:14:43.646 --> 01:14:46.982
Besides, maybe he can really sing.

01:14:46.983 --> 01:14:49.026
Yeah, sure. And maybe they'll vote me
King of the Prom.

01:14:52.989 --> 01:14:55.533
You know, you were right about him.

01:14:57.994 --> 01:14:59.286
He's not like anyone else.

01:15:01.956 --> 01:15:04.750
My mom says Stanley has something
most people will never have.

01:15:06.002 --> 01:15:07.503
Stanley has dignity.

01:15:09.755 --> 01:15:10.965
Yeah.

01:15:11.966 --> 01:15:14.552
Well, I gotta get back.

01:15:32.028 --> 01:15:34.739
<i>Next up is Janet Piccolo,</i>

01:15:34.864 --> 01:15:40.327
<i>who will twirl her baton to
the stirring Stars and Stripes Forever.</i>

01:15:40.703 --> 01:15:41.954
<i>Janefl</i>

01:15:46.876 --> 01:15:49.295
<i>(STARS AND STRIPES FOREVER
PLAYING)</i>

01:15:55.468 --> 01:15:57.553
(AUDIENCE CLAPPING
RHYTHMICALLY)

01:16:02.475 --> 01:16:03.726
There you go.

01:16:14.403 --> 01:16:15.529
Hey.

01:16:17.114 --> 01:16:18.783
Hello, Norman.

01:16:20.284 --> 01:16:21.577
Good luck.

01:16:23.079 --> 01:16:24.288
Thanks for coming.

01:16:24.371 --> 01:16:25.790
You Okay?

01:16:26.999 --> 01:16:28.626
Yeah. I think so.

01:16:29.085 --> 01:16:30.961
I'll see you after the show.

01:16:31.629 --> 01:16:32.838
Okay.

01:16:33.839 --> 01:16:36.842
Just... Can you tell me
why you think you have to do all this?

01:16:40.554 --> 01:16:42.098
Because, Norman, I'm a singer.

01:16:43.349 --> 01:16:44.433
That's what I am.

01:16:48.437 --> 01:16:49.647
Okay.

01:17:00.991 --> 01:17:02.868
(PLAYING ROCK MUSIC)

01:17:09.166 --> 01:17:10.751
(AUDIENCE CLAPPING)

01:17:13.129 --> 01:17:17.091
<i>Well... That was certainly interesting.</i>

01:17:18.843 --> 01:17:20.553
<i>For our next act,</i>

01:17:21.220 --> 01:17:26.142
<i>please welcome Tommy Kenner
and his swinging drum solo.</i>

01:17:30.896 --> 01:17:33.149
He's after Tommy Kenner.
I didn't know he played the drums.

01:17:33.232 --> 01:17:35.609
NORMAN: He's gotta be doing
something in his spare time.

01:17:35.693 --> 01:17:36.819
He certainly doesn't study.

01:17:36.902 --> 01:17:38.863
The guy can hardly walk and chew gum.

01:17:38.988 --> 01:17:41.574
Maybe he'll stink and Stanley
won't seem so bad in comparison.

01:17:46.662 --> 01:17:49.665
(PLAYING FUNKY BEAT)

01:18:01.010 --> 01:18:03.929
Holy crap! If Kenner could read
as well as he plays those drums,

01:18:04.054 --> 01:18:05.139
he'd be president.

01:18:19.737 --> 01:18:21.614
He doesn't stink nearly enough.

01:18:33.626 --> 01:18:35.294
(WHOOPING)

01:18:39.215 --> 01:18:41.175
Let the hanging begin.

01:18:50.226 --> 01:18:53.687
<i>My goodness gracious!
That certainly was something.</i>

01:18:54.438 --> 01:18:57.858
<i>All right, all right.
All right, folks. Calm down.</i>

01:18:58.108 --> 01:19:00.152
<i>Our show isn't over yet!</i>

01:19:01.237 --> 01:19:04.114
<i>For our last act of the show,</i>

01:19:04.782 --> 01:19:09.245
<i>Stanley Minor will sing a composition
which he wrote himself.</i>

01:19:09.286 --> 01:19:11.121
He wrote his own song?

01:19:11.205 --> 01:19:14.291
Go Ahead and Dream.

01:19:15.125 --> 01:19:17.503
If I was really his friend,
I would have killed him by now.

01:19:19.004 --> 01:19:21.173
ANDY: <i>Despite Norman's
passionate prayers,</i>

01:19:21.257 --> 01:19:23.259
<i>Big G walked out on the stage.</i>

01:19:23.968 --> 01:19:26.387
<i>Tall, straight, and proud.</i>

01:19:27.179 --> 01:19:30.140
<i>Like a man who had
every right to be there.</i>

01:19:31.725 --> 01:19:33.519
(GIRLS GIGGLING)

01:19:39.191 --> 01:19:40.526
<i>Excuse me, everyone.</i>

01:19:41.527 --> 01:19:42.611
<i>Excuse me!</i>

01:19:42.736 --> 01:19:47.950
<i>If we could all give Stanley
our undivided attention, please.</i>

01:19:49.159 --> 01:19:51.996
<i>He'll be singing without accompaniment,</i>

01:19:52.621 --> 01:19:55.708
<i>and we need it to be absolutely quiet.</i>

01:20:03.299 --> 01:20:06.385
You try and throw that tomato, Ricky,
and I'm gonna stop you.

01:20:07.303 --> 01:20:08.554
You don't have the balls, Nichol.

01:20:14.184 --> 01:20:16.145
(GROANING)

01:20:16.312 --> 01:20:18.230
Now you don't have the balls.

01:20:18.731 --> 01:20:20.941
(SCREAMING)

01:20:32.077 --> 01:20:34.079
Ricky, have you had
a bowel movement today?

01:20:34.204 --> 01:20:36.081
Obviously, you're suffering
from gas pains.

01:20:36.206 --> 01:20:38.083
Tomatoes will do that to you, you know.

01:20:38.208 --> 01:20:39.877
Boys, would you help
my friend Ricky here out of the gym?

01:20:40.002 --> 01:20:43.547
He's not feeling well
and, you know, the show must go on.

01:20:44.798 --> 01:20:46.341
Everything's fine, folks!

01:20:46.342 --> 01:20:51.764
Let us all keep quiet, please, and
give Mr Minor our undivided attention.

01:20:51.847 --> 01:20:53.015
Thank you.

01:20:59.355 --> 01:21:00.564
Good job.

01:21:06.362 --> 01:21:08.072
Stanley? Go.

01:21:15.079 --> 01:21:17.873
<i>(SINGING) Go</i> ahead <i>and dream</i>

01:21:18.415 --> 01:21:22.795
<i>Don't be afraid to laugh when others cry</i>

01:21:23.087 --> 01:21:25.381
<i>To live instead of die</i>

01:21:25.881 --> 01:21:28.384
<i>Life ain't what it seems</i>

01:21:28.509 --> 01:21:32.388
<i>So go ahead and dream</i>

01:21:33.138 --> 01:21:34.515
He's not bad.

01:21:34.640 --> 01:21:37.393
He's no Tommy Kenner,
but he's not bad.

01:21:38.394 --> 01:21:39.853
No, he's just

01:21:41.522 --> 01:21:42.731
brave.

01:21:43.399 --> 01:21:46.318
<i>(SINGING)
'Cause life ain't what it seems</i>

01:21:46.693 --> 01:21:50.697
<i>So go ahead and dream</i>

01:21:51.657 --> 01:21:55.035
<i>Go ahead and run right into fear</i>

01:21:55.160 --> 01:21:59.123
<i>The answer is to clear your mind</i>

01:21:59.248 --> 01:22:02.334
ANDY: <i>Big G had</i> a <i>very nice voice.</i>

01:22:02.418 --> 01:22:05.504
<i>If his voice had been great,
it would have made it all so easy.</i>

01:22:05.629 --> 01:22:09.383
<i>The crowd would have stood
and cheered him, a thundering ovation.</i>

01:22:09.425 --> 01:22:12.428
<i>But such was not Stanley Minor's
lot in life.</i>

01:22:12.970 --> 01:22:16.056
Look at his face. Look how happy he is.

01:22:19.059 --> 01:22:21.520
ANDY: <i>But, oh,
did he sing with passion.</i>

01:22:21.895 --> 01:22:23.856
<i>The joy freedom brings.</i>

01:22:25.065 --> 01:22:28.861
<i>(SINGING) Go</i> ahead <i>and dream</i>

01:22:29.445 --> 01:22:31.321
<i>Dream</i>

01:22:31.447 --> 01:22:34.283
<i>Dream</i>

01:22:37.744 --> 01:22:39.413
(WHOOPS)

01:22:51.675 --> 01:22:53.469
Damn, he's got guts!

01:22:54.553 --> 01:22:56.096
You shouldn't swear, Norman.

01:23:05.814 --> 01:23:07.608
ANDY: <i>With all the excitement,
I had almost forgotten</i>

01:23:07.733 --> 01:23:10.152
<i>about my date with Mary.</i>

01:23:10.235 --> 01:23:14.490
<i>Postponing destiny had only managed
to drive my anxiety even higher.</i>

01:23:15.491 --> 01:23:18.452
<i>There was
one distinct advantage, however.</i>

01:23:18.494 --> 01:23:23.332
<i>This time, I would enter the tunnel,
not under the protection of Mary Clear,</i>

01:23:23.999 --> 01:23:26.793
<i>but after having dealt
with Ricky Brown on my own.</i>

01:23:36.386 --> 01:23:37.513
Hi, Andy.

01:23:37.971 --> 01:23:39.139
Hi, Mary.

01:23:39.223 --> 01:23:42.518
ANDY: <i>She stood still,
allowing me the first advance.</i>

01:23:42.935 --> 01:23:46.563
<i>She held the faint wisps
of my tender male ego in her hand,</i>

01:23:46.647 --> 01:23:49.858
<i>and I could only hope
that she would caress them gently.</i>

01:23:58.075 --> 01:24:00.536
So, how're you doing?

01:24:00.994 --> 01:24:02.538
No, no. Uh...

01:24:03.372 --> 01:24:04.456
Let's forget that.

01:24:05.958 --> 01:24:08.377
So... Can I kiss you?

01:24:10.045 --> 01:24:11.213
Sure.

01:24:11.296 --> 01:24:14.216
<i>ANDY". Finally. I leaned in and kissed...</i>

01:24:14.299 --> 01:24:15.634
<i>Oh, no!</i>

01:24:15.759 --> 01:24:18.387
<i>At the last moment, I chickened out
and kissed her on the cheek,</i>

01:24:18.470 --> 01:24:21.265
<i>an appalling display of cowardice, and
she would have been within her rights</i>

01:24:21.390 --> 01:24:23.558
<i>to run around the school
laughing her head off.</i>

01:24:23.559 --> 01:24:26.270
You've never made out before,
have you?

01:24:26.395 --> 01:24:29.564
ANDY: <i>Male ego being what it is,
I might have lied to save face,</i>

01:24:29.565 --> 01:24:32.818
<i>but Mary seemed all-knowing somehow.</i>

01:24:33.443 --> 01:24:35.112
<i>Besides, who was I kidding?</i>

01:24:35.237 --> 01:24:36.321
No.

01:24:38.240 --> 01:24:40.075
Would you like me to teach you?

01:24:42.286 --> 01:24:44.705
Yes. I'd like that very much.

01:24:45.789 --> 01:24:47.499
<i>ANDY". And so she did.</i>

01:24:47.583 --> 01:24:52.583
<i>Slowly, carefully, handling me
as if I were a mound of clay</i>

01:24:52.588 --> 01:24:55.424
<i>moulded by the artist's tender touch.</i>

01:24:55.549 --> 01:24:57.884
<i>She turned what might have been
a scarring boyhood memory</i>

01:24:58.010 --> 01:25:00.596
<i>into the sweetest of recollections.</i>

01:25:00.679 --> 01:25:03.599
<i>And for that I would always be grateful.</i>

01:25:05.350 --> 01:25:06.810
What's with the stopwatch?

01:25:06.893 --> 01:25:11.064
I like to time each kiss.
The record is 1 minute and 16 seconds.

01:25:11.857 --> 01:25:13.066
Can I ask who holds the record?

01:25:13.150 --> 01:25:14.318
Ricky Brown.

01:25:15.485 --> 01:25:16.695
Figures.

01:25:16.820 --> 01:25:20.282
Well, if it helps, I can hold my breath
underwater for a minute and a half.

01:25:20.365 --> 01:25:22.034
That should help.

01:25:23.577 --> 01:25:25.954
(STOPWATCH TICKING)

01:25:36.715 --> 01:25:41.136
"I have finished my story of Joan of Arc,
that wonderful child,

01:25:41.637 --> 01:25:43.847
"that sublime personality,

01:25:44.348 --> 01:25:48.685
"that spirit which in one regard
has had no peer and will have none.

01:25:49.519 --> 01:25:53.398
"With Joan of Arc love of country
was more than a sentiment.

01:25:53.523 --> 01:25:55.275
"It was a passion.

01:25:55.359 --> 01:25:57.402
"She was the genius of patriotism,

01:25:58.487 --> 01:26:03.950
"love, mercy, charity, fortitude,
war, peace, poetry, music.

01:26:04.660 --> 01:26:07.663
"These may be symbolised
as any shall prefer,

01:26:07.913 --> 01:26:10.791
"by figures of either sex and of any age.

01:26:11.625 --> 01:26:14.670
"But a slender girl
in her first young bloom,

01:26:14.753 --> 01:26:16.797
"with the martyr's crown upon her head,

01:26:16.922 --> 01:26:20.801
"and in her hand the sword
that severed her country's bonds,

01:26:21.343 --> 01:26:25.680
"shall not this, and no other,
stand for patriotism

01:26:25.681 --> 01:26:29.226
"through all the ages,
until time shall end?"

01:26:33.313 --> 01:26:35.023
(ALL CHEERING)

01:26:46.410 --> 01:26:49.746
It really is a beautiful book, isn't it?
I hope you've all enjoyed it.

01:26:51.164 --> 01:26:54.751
All right, I have your papers here.
Your final team papers.

01:26:54.835 --> 01:27:00.215
And I would like to say, all in all,
that each team did a marvellous job.

01:27:00.465 --> 01:27:02.342
Congratulations to all of you.

01:27:02.634 --> 01:27:05.846
I would like each team to pick up
your paper on the way out.

01:27:05.971 --> 01:27:08.724
But before that, I just want to tell you,

01:27:08.765 --> 01:27:13.437
I have very much enjoyed
our time together this year,

01:27:14.020 --> 01:27:18.733
and I wish each and every one of you
all the best of luck

01:27:18.734 --> 01:27:20.736
as you enter high school next fall.

01:27:21.236 --> 01:27:22.446
(BELL RINGING)

01:27:22.571 --> 01:27:24.156
Class dismissed.

01:27:27.659 --> 01:27:28.994
Here you go.

01:27:31.288 --> 01:27:32.748
Very nice.

01:27:35.667 --> 01:27:36.793
<i>ANDY". In case you're wondering,</i>

01:27:36.877 --> 01:27:39.671
<i>Mary Clear and I went steady
for five weeks,</i>

01:27:39.755 --> 01:27:42.299
<i>her longest relationship to that point.</i>

01:27:42.424 --> 01:27:44.092
<i>It was a torrid affair.</i>

01:27:44.217 --> 01:27:46.636
<i>Kissing became even more enjoyable
when I discovered</i>

01:27:46.720 --> 01:27:48.805
<i>it was all right to breathe.</i>

01:27:52.184 --> 01:27:53.768
This was just wonderful.

01:27:53.769 --> 01:27:54.895
Thank you.

01:27:55.854 --> 01:27:57.647
Boys, you did a good job.

01:27:57.731 --> 01:27:59.441
- Thank you, Mr Simon.
-Thank you.

01:27:59.524 --> 01:28:01.318
<i>ANDY: And as for Mr Simon...</i>

01:28:02.778 --> 01:28:04.654
Wow! Thank you, sir.

01:28:05.864 --> 01:28:07.199
Thank you, sir.

01:28:07.282 --> 01:28:10.702
I am as proud of you two boys
as any students I've ever had.

01:28:11.620 --> 01:28:12.788
And I mean that.

01:28:12.871 --> 01:28:15.999
And I wish you both
a wonderful summer

01:28:16.082 --> 01:28:17.542
and a wonderful life.

01:28:19.127 --> 01:28:21.797
What are you going
to do now, Mr Simon?

01:28:21.838 --> 01:28:25.008
Well, I'll find some place to teach,
of course.

01:28:27.511 --> 01:28:28.678
I am a teacher.

01:28:29.805 --> 01:28:30.931
That's what I am.

01:28:32.432 --> 01:28:33.558
Goodbye, sir.

01:28:33.683 --> 01:28:34.893
Goodbye, Stanley.

01:28:38.063 --> 01:28:39.481
Goodbye, Andrew.

01:28:39.564 --> 01:28:41.024
Goodbye, sir. Thank you.

01:28:58.750 --> 01:29:00.794
ANDY: <i>Stanley and I lost touch
when he moved away</i>

01:29:00.836 --> 01:29:02.504
<i>in our sophomore year in high school.</i>

01:29:02.838 --> 01:29:06.508
<i>I can assure you his suffering
did not end in the eighth grade.</i>

01:29:06.967 --> 01:29:10.762
<i>Nevertheless, I know whatever
hardships were thrust upon him,</i>

01:29:11.263 --> 01:29:12.848
<i>he handled them with dignity.</i>

01:29:12.889 --> 01:29:14.307
He's coming.

01:29:14.391 --> 01:29:17.686
<i>As for me, well, I am a writer.</i>

01:29:17.978 --> 01:29:19.855
<i>That's what I am.</i>

01:29:23.900 --> 01:29:25.694
Against the wall! Against the wall!

01:29:25.944 --> 01:29:28.154
<i>And with my pen, I can create a world</i>

01:29:28.280 --> 01:29:30.907
<i>where brave men like Stanley Minor
are exalted</i>

01:29:30.991 --> 01:29:34.411
<i>as the standard by which
we all measure ourselves,</i>

01:29:34.536 --> 01:29:38.206
a <i>world where Karen Connor
will fit the glass slipper,</i>

01:29:38.331 --> 01:29:41.543
<i>and Norman Grunmeyer
is voted King of the Prom,</i>

01:29:42.127 --> 01:29:43.545
<i>a world where the equation</i>

01:29:43.628 --> 01:29:47.382
<i>human dignity plus compassion
equals peace.</i>

01:30:08.737 --> 01:30:10.864
One, two, three!

01:30:10.906 --> 01:30:13.825
ALL: Goodbye, Mr Simon!

01:30:14.159 --> 01:30:15.785
(ALL CHEERING)

01:30:19.915 --> 01:30:21.207
Thank you!

01:30:24.794 --> 01:30:26.379
Thank you! Yeah!

01:30:28.924 --> 01:30:30.675
Best teacher ever!

01:30:47.567 --> 01:30:50.779
Thank you! You're the best! The best!

01:31:07.963 --> 01:31:09.589
Hey, Stanley!

01:31:17.430 --> 01:31:18.974
See you around.

01:31:21.101 --> 01:31:22.978
See you around, Andy.

01:31:36.241 --> 01:31:39.452
ANDY: <i>The last week of eighth grade
was memorable for many reasons,</i>

01:31:39.536 --> 01:31:43.331
<i>not the least of which were those
glorious make-out sessions with Mary.</i>

01:31:43.456 --> 01:31:47.711
<i>But knowing I would never
see Mr Simon again haunted me.</i>

01:31:47.836 --> 01:31:51.214
<i>There was still one question
that had to be answered.</i>

01:32:04.519 --> 01:32:05.937
Mr Simon?

01:32:12.360 --> 01:32:14.029
Hello? Mr Simon?

01:32:30.336 --> 01:32:31.713
Can I help you, Mr Nichol?

01:32:33.048 --> 01:32:34.090
I'm so sorry, sir.

01:32:34.174 --> 01:32:36.301
It's okay. I'm glad you dropped by.

01:32:37.510 --> 01:32:38.720
Would you like a cup of tea?

01:32:39.012 --> 01:32:40.138
No, sir, thank you.

01:32:40.889 --> 01:32:42.891
I just wanted to ask you a question.

01:32:42.974 --> 01:32:44.601
My wife, yes.

01:32:47.062 --> 01:32:48.563
Mystery solved?

01:32:49.105 --> 01:32:50.565
No, sir.

01:32:52.025 --> 01:32:53.151
Well...

01:32:53.485 --> 01:32:55.069
Yeah. I guess that, too.

01:32:55.070 --> 01:32:56.529
Have a seat.

01:32:59.699 --> 01:33:01.618
So, where is she?

01:33:02.077 --> 01:33:06.289
She passed away,
19 years ago today, in fact.

01:33:09.334 --> 01:33:10.543
I'm sorry.

01:33:10.627 --> 01:33:13.088
Yeah. A little sappy, I'm afraid.

01:33:13.505 --> 01:33:16.800
As a writer, it would do you well
to avoid melodrama in your work.

01:33:18.968 --> 01:33:22.013
I suppose I loved her too much.

01:33:25.100 --> 01:33:27.143
Does that help you, Andrew?

01:33:27.227 --> 01:33:28.353
No.

01:33:28.436 --> 01:33:32.524
I mean, I don't care about that.
That's not why I came.

01:33:33.441 --> 01:33:35.109
Oh, really?

01:33:35.110 --> 01:33:37.821
Well, you've got me intrigued.
What is it?

01:33:39.364 --> 01:33:43.409
I just wanted to know, when you
assigned me to work with Stanley,

01:33:43.535 --> 01:33:44.619
Why'd you pick me?

01:33:44.744 --> 01:33:47.122
You said there was a reason.

01:33:47.163 --> 01:33:53.128
Well, I believe that life is about timing,
opportunity, and choices.

01:33:54.045 --> 01:33:56.131
It was an opportunity at the right time

01:33:56.172 --> 01:34:00.009
for a wonderful young man like you
to make the right choice.

01:34:00.093 --> 01:34:04.681
And I knew you weren't ready to do that,

01:34:04.806 --> 01:34:07.183
but I didn't want you to miss it.

01:34:08.393 --> 01:34:12.689
But how did you know it would work?
How did you know that I could do it?

01:34:13.481 --> 01:34:14.899
I didn't.

01:34:15.233 --> 01:34:19.779
But sometimes you just need someone
to tell you that you can.

01:34:21.447 --> 01:34:24.159
ANDY: <i>I'm not sure
that I fully understood it then,</i>

01:34:24.242 --> 01:34:26.035
<i>but it did occur to me that somewhere</i>

01:34:26.119 --> 01:34:30.206
<i>in that marvellous pile of books
Mr Simon cherished,</i>

01:34:30.290 --> 01:34:33.793
<i>there was</i> a <i>manual
called How</i> to <i>Be</i> a <i>Teacher</i>

01:34:33.877 --> 01:34:35.670
<i>written by Mr Simon.</i>

01:35:01.487 --> 01:35:04.199
Andy! Andy! Shut it off! Come on!

01:35:05.033 --> 01:35:07.160
Shut it Off! Shut it Off!

01:35:07.952 --> 01:35:09.204
Come on.

01:35:09.704 --> 01:35:11.205
Now, how many times have I told you?

01:35:11.206 --> 01:35:13.416
You have to use the wheel grooves
as a guide

01:35:13.499 --> 01:35:15.752
to show where you left off!
Here. I'll show you!

01:35:15.877 --> 01:35:17.670
No, no! No.

01:35:19.214 --> 01:35:21.216
What do you mean, "No"?

01:35:24.219 --> 01:35:25.553
I mean...

01:35:25.678 --> 01:35:27.680
I'm going to finish the lawn, Dad.

01:35:27.764 --> 01:35:31.059
I'll go over it again
and catch anything I missed.

01:35:31.142 --> 01:35:32.226
That's just the way I do it.

01:35:32.227 --> 01:35:35.104
Once one way,
and then another against the grain.

01:35:35.188 --> 01:35:38.316
Like at the ballpark,
or like a checkerboard!

01:35:40.735 --> 01:35:43.154
I like to do it, Dad.
I like to mow the lawn.

01:35:43.238 --> 01:35:47.242
I like the way it looks and smells,
and I'm going to finish it.

01:35:47.283 --> 01:35:48.493
My Way!

01:35:48.576 --> 01:35:52.497
Then, once I'm done, if I've still left
a spot, you can call me a jughead.

01:35:52.580 --> 01:35:55.250
But please, just let me finish.

01:36:00.338 --> 01:36:01.547
Okay.

01:36:05.510 --> 01:36:07.136
Fair enough.

01:36:08.221 --> 01:36:09.264
What?

